<HEADLINE>
A RELIEF PHONE LINE 
</HEADLINE>
  (sw) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ The Agency for International Development has
established a toll-free telephone number and Internet site to
encourage charitable donations to private groups helping to feed
and shelter the hundreds of thousands of refugees who have streamed
out of Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
   Callers to the telephone number (1-800-USAID-RELIEF, or
1-800-872-4373) and visitors to the site (www.info.usaid.gov) are
provided with a list of charitable organizations working along
Kosovo's borders.
</P>
<P>
   The agency, the lead government organization in the humanitarian
aid effort for the refugees, is encouraging donors to offer money
to the groups, rather than collecting clothing or food.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
