<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BBN-DODGERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MONDESI SAVES DAY FOR DODGERS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ More than three months of anticipation collided
with the start of six months of expectations on a made-for-baseball
afternoon Monday at Dodger Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   The impact produced a stirring opening day, and to everyone's
surprise, it had nothing to do with Kevin Brown or Randy Johnson.
Instead, it was Dodgers right fielder Raul Mondesi reminding
everyone just how talented he can be and how quickly he can change
a game.
</P>
<P>
   Mondesi homered with two outs in the ninth inning to tie the
score, then smashed a two-run homer with two outs in the 11th to
give the Dodgers an 8-6 win against the Arizona Diamondbacks before
a sellout crowd of 53,109. Mondesi tied a career-high with six RBI.
</P>
<P>
   ``People expect us to win,'' Dodgers second baseman Eric Young
said. ``To come out and win in that fashion, it's a big thing for
us.''
</P>
<P>
   For a day, at least, the momentum the Dodgers began building
when they inked Devon White on the first day of the free-agent
signing period last November continued.
</P>
<P>
   They have Mondesi to thank for that. ``This is about as good a
game you're going to have on opening day,'' Dodgers first baseman
Eric Karros said. ``The hype, the expectations, the pitching
matchup _ it's about as good as opening day can be.''
</P>
<P>
   The Diamondbacks talked all spring about their own offseason
acquisitions and how they will contend for the NL West Division
crown. So much so that Dodgers manager Davey Johnson said Arizona
was ``cocky'' about its chances.
</P>
<P>
   In rallying from a 6-2 deficit in the eighth inning, the Dodgers
landed the first blow of what could be many exchanges between the
clubs.
</P>
<P>
   The comeback began on Karros' RBI single in the eighth that made
it 6-3. It picked up steam an inning later when Jose Vizcaino led
off with an infield single and pinch-hitter Dave Hansen singled
with one out. That's when Diamondbacks closer Gregg Olson, who was
30 of 34 in save opportunities last season, was summoned.
</P>
<P>
   Though he struck out Gary Sheffield, Olson's inability to throw
strikes to Mondesi cost him the game. Awaiting to unload on a 3-0
fastball anywhere near the plate, Mondesi smashed the high pitch he
later called ball four into the Dodgers' bullpen to tie it at 6.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Manager Davey Johnson) gave me the green light, but I didn't
see the sign,'' said Mondesi, who was 4 for 5. ``If it was close, I
was going to try to hit it. Anything close to the zone, I was going
to take a swing. First game, we're losing by three runs, to hit a
home run, it's exciting.''
</P>
<P>
   Two innings later the excitement reached euphoria. Mondesi ended
the game when he drove John Frascatore's 1-0 fastball into the
left-field bleachers. Frascatore (0-1) took the loss; the Dodgers'
Jeff Shaw (1-0) pitched two perfect innings for the win.
</P>
<P>
   ``We came back from the dead,'' Johnson said. ``Both (homers)
were crushed. I started shaking hands when he hit (the second one).
It's a great way to get out of the chute in front of a full
house.''
</P>
<P>
   It's also something the Dodgers needed. In the scope of a
162-game season, one game might not seem like a big deal. But with
the expectations placed on the Dodgers _ by themselves, the fans
and the media _ it was certainly a good way to begin their 41st
season in Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   Especially since their $105 million free-agent signing, a.k.a.
Kevin Brown, was booed after giving up his third homer and being
yanked in the sixth inning. Brown allowed five runs _ on a pair of
solo homers by Bernard Gilkey and a three-run shot by Jay Bell _ on
10 hits in 52/3 innings.
</P>
<P>
   ``If this team loses, it's really difficult because I didn't do
my job,'' Brown said. ``You never want to pitch bad, but it's a lot
easier to swallow if you come back and win.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-06-99 0026EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
