<P>
   CAMPAIGN-FINANCE (Palm Beach, Fla.) _ Former Sen. Bill Bradley
of New Jersey devoted years to scorning the campaign finance
system, but that has not deterred him from partaking in it himself.
Sen. John McCain of Arizona is also known for championing campaign
reform, but there he was the other day at a fund-raising brunch at
a classy restaurant. Both argue that the existing laws leave them
no choice but to devote much time to traveling the country hunting
for millions of dollars needed to run for president. By Richard L.
Berke.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-LORTEL (Undated) _ Lucille Lortel, whose pioneering efforts
to bring innovative theater and adventurous new playwrights and
actors to the American stage earned her the title Queen of Off
Broadway, died on Sunday at New York Presbyterian Hospital in
Manhattan. She was 98 and had homes in Manhattan and Westport,
Conn. By Enid Nemy.
</P>
