<HEADLINE>
LAKERS WITHSTAND VAN EXEL'S BIG NIGHT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD _ Nick Van Exel and Lakers turmoil go together like
Bill and Monica _ even with the feisty point guard playing in
Nuggets gear and even though the coach he feuded with was impeached
several weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
   So it was only natural that Van Exel arrived in Los Angeles with
the Lakers reeling from their abomination against Golden State,
wading ankle-deep in self-doubt, and Nick the Quick aiming to stick
another pin in their sinking raft.
</P>
<P>
   The Forum not-so-faithful almost seemed to root for it. Van Exel
was greeted with warm cheers and a ``We Miss U Nick'' sign. The
Lakers were again doused with a round of boos in a raggedy first
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   Nick and turmoil, turmoil and Nick.
</P>
<P>
   But Van Exel couldn't single-handedly prolong the Lakers'
misery, though he tried his darndest. Just shy of a triple-double,
Van Exel scored a career-high 41 points, but the Lakers rode
resurgent shooting from Kobe Bryant and Glen Rice to take a 117-104
victory.
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel had already embarrassed his ex-mates once this season,
leading a Nuggets overtime victory in late February that helped
hasten the dismissal of his nemesis, coach Del Harris.
</P>
<P>
   A sequel seemed to be in the works when Van Exel got loose for
18 points in the first half and the foul-stricken Shaquille O'Neal
sat on the bench. But Rice kept the Lakers alive, scoring 20 of his
season-high 26 points in the first half, and Bryant finished it off
by scoring 20 of his 26 points in the second half.
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel had to pack up his turmoil and go home with the
Nuggets' 0-17 road record, and 24th consecutive road loss, dating
back to last season. Any trash talking or message sending would be
moot.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was trying to get a win. What message can you send when
you've won 10 games and haven't won on the road all year?'' he
said.
</P>
<P>
   So leave the barbs to the Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   ``If he always played like that,'' O'Neal said, ``he would still
be here.''
</P>
<P>
   And the Lakers were willing to give up a career game to Van Exel
so long as they contained everyone else. Dennis Rodman, between
grabbing 17 rebounds, helped hold Antonio McDyess to 11 points on
4-of-14 shooting. And after a big first half, Chauncey Billups was
held to 15.
</P>
<P>
   As for Van Exel's replacements, the Dereks did their job _
Harper and Fisher combined for 17 points and 16 assists. The team's
33 assists were a season high, the eight turnovers a season low.
</P>
<P>
   And Van Exel's inspired performance, not at all unexpected.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm sure he definitely enjoyed coming back,'' Fisher said.
``Nick, he thrives off of people not liking him or the odds being
against him. Tonight, it was him and the Nuggets against the
world.... He wanted to come out and put on a show.''
</P>
<P>
   But by the end of the game, the fans had turned against Van Exel
again and in favor of the guys still wearing purple and gold,
alternately chanting for Rodman and especially Bryant, who saved
the Lakers from another Van Exel burst.
</P>
<P>
   Van Exel's running jumper closed the gap to four points early in
the fourth, then Bryant got hot, scoring 17 points _ including 4 of
4 3-pointers _ in the final 11 minutes.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman, for one, wasn't getting carried away with the win.
</P>
<P>
   ``We can't pat ourselves on the back, because it is a bad team
we played tonight,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
