</P>
<P>
   _ Four minutes of exercise four times a week for fitness is the
claim of a company selling a new device. Two studies give
conflicting results of its effectiveness, but most major exercise
experts dismiss the device. (500 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ The American Academy of Pediatrics has begun recommending that
all infants be checked at birth for hearing loss. In a statement
issued in February, the academy said that prompt diagnosis of
hearing problems can help offset lapses in language development.
(350 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ For people wanting the have the millennium's first baby, April
9 is the day, say experts say. But others acknowledge it's simply a
crap shoot. (275 words)
</P>
<P>
   _ New research confirms that boys overestimate their academic
ability, while girls underestimate it. It also shows that the gap
widens and suggests that depression may be the root of the girls'
lack of esteem. (350 words)
</P>
<P>
   SCI-Q&AMP;A (Undated) _ Science questions answered: Why is your
blood type _ A, B, AB or O _ so important? The most basic
classification of the hundreds of ways to type human blood, the ABO
system, is important because incompatible types of blood react with
each other to form sticky globs of red blood cells that can cause
serious and sometimes fatal circulation blockage. (300 words)
</P>
