   O'HAIR-MISSING (San Antonio) _ A Michigan ex-convict being
investigated in connection with Madalyn Murray O'Hair's 1995
disappearance has admitted involvement in four Texas homicides, at
least one of which involved decapitation and mutilation, an FBI
agent testified. By JOHN MacCORMACK.
</P>
<P>
   ANTI-GAY-VIOLENCE (San Francisco) _ Serious gay-related hate
violence _ including homicides _ increased dramatically in the past
year, according to national and local statistics released by a San
Francisco advocacy group. By MARIANNE COSTANTIOU.
</P>
<P>
   UNDERGROUND-TANKS (San Francisco) _ Gasoline and the possibly
cancer-causing fuel additive MTBE continue to ooze from some
underground gasoline tanks and pipes that were repaired or replaced
at owners' expense to meet a 1998 legal deadline, according to a
yearlong study by the State Water Resources Control Board. By JANE
KAY.
</P>
<P>
   UNIVERSITY-MARKETING (Troy, N.Y.) _ ``Where's the beef?'' ``Got
milk?'' To these indelible advertising questions, Rensselaer
Polytechnic Institute hopes to add ``Why not change the world?''
That's the centerpiece of a marketing blitz aimed at making RPI a
competitor of research powerhouses like Stanford University and the
Massachusetts Institute of Technology. By ANDREW BROWNSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   GASOLINE-PRICES (San Francisco) _ Although California refineries
are now producing more gasoline than a year ago, the age-old laws
of supply and demand _ and upcoming summer vacations _ are expected
to keep prices high at California pumps in the immediate future. By
KATHLEEN SULLIVAN and GEORGE RAINE.
</P>
<P>
   SECURITY-CHECKS (San Francisco) _ A member of this city's Board
of Supervisors wants board members granted the privilege of
bypassing the security checkpoints at City Hall _ protections that
were tightened after a former supervisor assassinated two men,
including the mayor, in their offices two decades ago. By RACHEL
GORDON.
</P>
<P>
   LIFESTYLE/FEATURES (``l'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FIBER-DIET (Albany, N.Y.) _ For decades, doctors have known that
fiber is the foundation of any healthy diet. Here are some tips on
how to get more fiber and achieve a more balanced diet. By SYLVIA
WOOD.
</P>
<P>
   HOSE-NOZZLES (Albany, N.Y.) _ A pass through the garden section
of any home center or hardware store will confirm that watering
your lawn, shrubs, flowers and garden has become both art and
science. A variety of garden hose spray nozzles can meet your every
watering need, and in most cases they are all contained in one
hand-held adjustable tool. By FRANCES INGRAHAM.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-YANKEES-ZIMMER (Tampa, Fla.) _ Don Zimmer, 68, is
temporarily manager of the New York Yankees. So is he having fun
yet? The answer is no, but he's doing the job for an old friend,
Joe Torre, who is recovering from prostate surgery. ``There will be
nobody in the world ... who will be happier when he comes back,''
Zimmer says. By STEVE CAMPBELL.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLACK-COLUMN (San Antonio) _ I believe that only through a
commitment to nonviolence can the scourges of poverty, war and
hatred be overcome, that only nonviolence can break the manacled
chain of violence. Yet I support, reluctantly, the NATO bombing of
Yugoslavia as a way to stop the ethnic cleansing in Kosovo. By CARY
CLACK.
</P>
