   MO-GUNS (St. Louis) _ Although 31 states allow citizens to carry
concealed weapons, Missouri has became the first state to put the
question before voters. The practice has been banned here since
1875, when outlaw Jesse James was still at large. By Dirk Johnson.
</P>
