<HEADLINE>
NOURISHMENT FOR THE BODY AND THE SOUL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JERRY MORRIS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   One of the heavenly rewards I enjoy each morning is a muffin
smothered with red raspberry jam made by the monks at St. Joseph's
Abbey in Spencer, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   The jams are sold in supermarkets but it can be a far more
fulfilling experience to visit the Trappist monastery just outside
Worcester _ and, I'm not even Catholic.
</P>
<P>
   For many, a visit to a monastery or retreat house provides a
peaceful time to escape the outside world, a time for solitude that
leads to reflection and, perhaps, regeneration.
</P>
<P>
   In other venues, there are quiet places for travelers to explore
life changes ranging from holistic vacations to health
revitalizating spas, from self-improvement to educational
vacations.
</P>
<P>
   Fortunately there are places scattered about the country and
overseas that offer just such vacations. Four recent books provide
a gateway to finding just the right retreat or revitalizing
vacation:
</P>
<P>
   ``Vacations That Can Change Your Life'' by Ellen Lederman
(Sourcebooks, $16.95); ``The Whole Heaven Catalog'' by Marcia and
Jack Kelly (Crown, $18); and ``Bed and Blessings in Italy'' by June
and Anne Walsh (Paulist Press, $16.95); and ``Sanctuaries'' also by
the Kellys (Crown Publishing, $18).
</P>
<P>
   You'll find some surprises in these books. For example, while I
knew the Trappists take a vow of silence and are for men only,
couples and women can stay at the abbey for a retreat.
</P>
<P>
   On Cape Cod, the Society of Jesus was a mystery. Now I know it
is a society made up of members and clergy from various Protestant
denominations, and even offers Cape Codders services such as lawn
care and construction.
</P>
<P>
   It's located right in Orleans on the water. At most of the
retreats you don't have to be a member of a particular church, or
even sign up for a organized program.
</P>
<P>
   There are retreats for just about every religion, and every
need. For example, just a short distance from Spencer in Lenox is
Kripalu Center for Yoga and Health, which caters to meeting the
spiritual needs for the whole person from health to exercise to
meditation. It's near Tanglewood, the Boston Symphony Orchestra's
summer ``retreat'' center.
</P>
<P>
   ``Vacations That Can Change Your Life'' offers the greatest
variety of retreat or learning vacations. ``The Whole Heaven
Catalog,'' in addition to being a guide to retreat centers, offers
information to products made at a particular center along with
festivals to participate in.
</P>
<P>
   ``Sanctuaries'' and ``Bed and Blessings in Italy'' are limited
to being guides to retreat centers. The Italy guide is on Roman
Catholic centers, and provides a great source of accommodations for
anyone heading to Rome or elsewhere for the Holy Year of 2000.
``Sanctuaries'' covers retreat centers for all faiths.
</P>
<P>
   In addition to providing a place for reflection, these retreats
all provide low-cost accommodations. All the guides provide
complete information on locating the centers, along with costs,
types of accommodations, and whether the retreats are suitable for
families, singles or couples.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Going to church?
</P>
<P>
   Nearly 28 percent of adult travelers (43 million) in the United
States went to a church, temple, mosque or other place of worship
to attend a regularly scheduled religious service while on a trip
of 100 miles or more last year.
</P>
<P>
   The travel industry survey reported in the Newport County
Gateway said the poll did not include travelers who went to a place
of worship for sightseeing or to attend a special service such as a
wedding or bar mitzvah.
</P>
<P>
   Newport is marking the 350th anniversary of the founding of
Trinity Church, and is also home to the nation's oldest synagogue.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
Taxing times
</P>
<P>
   Looking for ways to ease the tax bite? New York's Barbizon Hotel
&AMP; Towers has an interesting Tortured by Taxes package for April 14.
</P>
<P>
   The hotel's suites will be equipped with a lap top computer
fully-loaded with Intuit's Turbo Tax, a copy of Taxes for Dummies
will be available as well as a paper shredder for you know what,
and an IRS Voodoo doll with assorted pins and needles for stress
relief.
</P>
<P>
   In the morning, show your completed tax form and a $50
contribution will be made in your name to a charity of your choice
and it's good for a '99 tax deduction. Also included is a spa
therapy relaxation treatment. The package is $475; for information
call 800-223-1020.
</P>
</TEXT>
