embraces many ethnic dishes from a dizzying number of regions,
there is still one major Asian cuisine so unknown to many New
Yorkers it's as if it's meant to be a secret. And it almost is.
Korean food _ bold-spirited, healthful, a treasure for the
adventurous among us _ has been reserved almost exclusively for
