<HEADER>
A7724 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-INDECISION-TIPS-LADN     04-06 0304
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-INDECISION-TIPS-LADN </SLUG>
 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CAROL BIDWELL  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ On the average, American adults make 73 decisions
every day _ 39 at work, 11 about purchases and 23 involving home
and family, according to a survey conducted by the New Jersey-based
Opinion Research Corp.
</P>
<P>
   Forty-seven percent of both men and women questioned said they
feel more empowered making a decision once they have all the facts.
</P>
<P>
   But at some point, reflection and study becomes indecisiveness.
</P>
<P>
   And indecisiveness isn't a quest for perfection, it's fear of
making a mistake, according to British management consultant Robert
Heller in his new book, ``Making Decisions'' (DK Publishing;
$6.95). Although the 72-page volume was written as a quick lesson
for managers on how to make effective business decisions, the
advice can be applied to just about any decision-making situation.
</P>
<P>
   ``Accept that every decision in life has a chance of error and
that no individual or organization can make progress by being
negative,'' Heller advises. ``Your fear of making a mistake can be
eliminated completely only if you never make a decision at all.
Instead of falling into this trap, take positive steps to
strengthen your confidence.''
</P>
<P>
   To move beyond indecision in your personal life, Heller advises
the following:
</P>
<P>
   _ Determine which decisions must be made quickly and which can
wait for more deliberation.
</P>
<P>
   _ Make a checklist of the issues, both pro and con.
</P>
<P>
   _ Weigh each alternative and determine how likely each is to
occur.
</P>
<P>
   _ Imagine the worst that could happen and whether you could live
with that result.
</P>
<P>
   _ Pick one of the alternatives and take action to implement it.
</P>
<P>
   _ Write down your fears and throw them in the trash. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-06-99 1422EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
