   GOP-KOSOVO (Washington) _ Reflecting American uncertainty
generally, Republican presidential candidates are all over the lot
on U.S. involvement in the Balkans. Pat Buchanan and Gary Bauer are
on the isolationist side while former Vietnam POW Sen. John McCain,
R-Ariz., says bombs away and don't rule out ground forces. By DAN
