been indicted by a federal grand jury for violating the terms of
his probation by possessing firearms and ammunition. The indictment
alleges that Waters, 52, shipped several handguns to Illinois just
days after a news report about the identification of a headless
corpse near Dallas. By JOHN MacCORMACK.
