main characters of golf in their most entertaining, enlightening
moments during the major championships. His new work, ``The
Majors,'' is a wonderful follow-up to his best-selling ``Good Walk
Spoiled.'' It's not often that you get to feel as though you're
eavesdropping on history. (Includes 3-column color photo of golf
players at Augusta National and two color photos of book jackets.)
</P>
