   PAGE WILL INCLUDE ONE COLOR PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   LUTHERAN: On Oct. 31, 1517, Martin Luther tacked a paper to the
Palace Church door in Wittenberg, sparking a movement that changed
Christianity. But the church Luther founded finds itself in deep
trouble in Europe, where the Lutheran World Federation reported a
``general reduction in numbers.'' And the problem is even greater
in Germany, the homeland of Protestanism, where more than a million
people have left the church rolls in the 1990s.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: CHURCH OF ENGLAND: The Church of England has become a
stodgy, picturesque part of the British Isles, a place tourists
visit, but few Brits actually are involved with.
