in data processing in 1958. Y2K has almost nothing to do with
computer memory and everything to do with storage media! If I
keypunch a two-digit century on an 80-column card, I have two fewer
bytes to put ``real'' data in it. If I include a two-digit century
on a tape record (there were few disks in the old days) that is
written at 200 characters per inch, I can waste a lot of tape!
