   WITH
</P>
<P>
   AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the BMW M Coupe.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP DRIVING _ The performance and personalities of stability
control systems are as varied as the brands that carry them.
(Sharp, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). Includes 1-column color
photograph of columnist Linda Sharp.
</P>
<P>
   (EDS: This is the CoxNet WHEELS page for the current week. This
layout is now available.)
</P>
<P>
   NETBANK _ Net.Bnk Inc. Chief Executive D.R. Grimes expects 100%
earnings per share growth this year. ``The analysts' expectations
this year are for about 100% earnings per share growth and about
90% next year. In February, Net.Bnk reported fiscal 1999 earnings
of 70 cents a diluted share, including a tax benefit of about 48
cents a share from prior tax losses. We talk to the company about
its stock's strategy and the stock's phenomenal growth. (Clothier,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
