</P>
<P>
   NETBANK-SIDE _ So, what's the difference in banking online and
banking with traditional institutions and where do you get the most
for your money? (Ezell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CHERRYCOKE-GAME _ Cherry Coke introduces another summertime
onlinr game called Time Tremors. This time out there's a huge
marketing promotion and even tournament play. Cherry Coke is one of
the smarter marketers on the Web with its summer seasonal promos.
(Katz, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   AOL-LEONSIS _ A Q and A with Ted Leonsis, AOL's No. 2 manager,
in advance of the AIM conference which starts April 12. Leonsis
will be keynoting the conference and discussing e-mail commerce, so
this will be the focus of the q and a. (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TORVALDS-QA _ A Q&AMP;A with Linus Torvalds, inventor of Linux
operating system, which is starting to scare mighty Microsoft.
Torvalds, 29, will be in town to speak to a trade group April
12-15. (Kannell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CELLTOWERS _ Metro Atlanta, with one of the highest penetration
of cellular devices of any city in the country, has more than one
thousand cell towers. These towers are in the news now because many
of them have been sold to a company which will lease them back to
their original owners and others for big bucks. The sales brought
in nearly $1 billion for the sellers and will bring in more than
that in revenue to the buyer. How valuable are these towers, how do
they work, and why don't we know where they are? Kanell, w/graphic
of tower and its revenue streams, as well as photos of church
steeples, etc., that play host to these valuable towers. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-GEORGIA _ No state has spent more on solving the Millennium
bug and had less to show for it so far than Georgia. That's the
conclusion of a recent survey by CIO, a magazine that caters to
corporate and government chief information officer. In its issue
dated April 1, CIO surveyed efforts by all 50 state governments.
Georgia ranked number one in terms of how much it has allocated so
far on Y2k. (Haddad, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   INTERNET _ Internet 2, the latest in high speed communication,
is up and running, with Georgia Tech as one of the lead players.
(Holsendolph, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TESTDRIVE-ALERO _ A review of the Oldsmobile Alero (DeVault),
Cox News Service).
</P>
