<P>
   DEFIBRILLATE-SURVIVAL (Undated) _ Getting defibrillators to the
scene within 8 minutes increases the survival rate of heart attack
victims by 30 percent, new study shows. By Larry Tye. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-TEACHERS (Boston) _ College association admits schools are
largely responsible for the failure rates on the Massachusetts
teacher certification tests, vows to work with state officials to
improve the quality and quantity of public school teachers. By Kate
Zernike. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MA-TOBACCO (Boston) _ As Massachusetts launches another fierce
anti-smoking commercial, it joins other states in trying to kill a
public service campaign funded by tobacco companies that is
considered ineffective and soft. By Frank Phillips. 700 words.
