<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, APRIL 7
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-FBI-INFORMER-NYT (moved on Friday, Mar. 12)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Mar. 12,
about organized-crime defendants and the F.B.I. in Boston referred
incompletely to the status of some defendants. While the
authorities say two defendants, Stephen Flemmi and James Bulger,
were informers for the F.B.I., there has never been any claim that
the other defendants in the case, Francis Salemme and Robert
DeLuca, ever served as informers.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SALON-AD-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Sunday, Apr. 4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 4,
about a redesign for the Salon Internet on-line magazine Salon,
misstated the name of the owner of a Web site that sold its address
to Salon. He is Roy Fredericks, not Frederickson. The article also
misidentified one magazine that will carry Salon's new
advertisements. It is The Atlantic Monthly, not American Monthly.
</P>
<P>
   The column also included an erroneous reference from Salon's
owners to advertising by the Saturn division of General Motors.
Saturn has ceased advertising on the site.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-NOTES-NYT (moved on Sunday, Apr .4)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Apr. 4,
about journalists' efforts to interview Sante and Kenneth Kimes, a
mother and son accused of killing a missing Upper East Side
millionaire, referred incorrectly to the payment of air fare and
hotel expenses for the Kimeses' defense lawyer, Mel A. Sachs, and a
colleague on a trip to Grand Cayman. They were not paid by the news
program ``Fox Files.''
</P>
</TEXT>
