Organization, but his advisers are deeply split about whether a
surprisingly broad set of concessions by the Chinese will be
sufficient to blunt tremendous opposition in Congress. By David E.
Sanger.
</P>
<P>
   (Story has moved.)
</P>
<P>
   Here are tonight's other regular features:
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY-AD-COLUMN _ A serious effort by marketers to urge more
``family friendly'' television programming has picked up speed,
with more than a score of leading advertisers now supporting plans
to stimulate producers to develop _ and networks to schedule _ such
shows. By Stuart Elliott.
</P>
<P>
   BIZGLANCE (Undated) _ Digest of the day's financial stories.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
