-- Avi Pazner, right, a Holocaust survivor and the first Israeli
Ambassador to Albania, offers an apple to a child at a refugee tent
camp in Tirana. ``I feel like I'm going back in time,'' says
Pazner, clearly moved by the scene. ``I feel so close to these
people.'' (Rina Castelnuovo/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT13) NEW YORK -- April 6, 1999 --
SOUTH-PACIFIC-ANNIVERSARY-2-B&AMP;W, 04-06 -- Jackie Langee, fourth
from left, in the 1949 production of Rodgers and Hammerstein's
``South Pacific.'' Mary Martin is at center, foreground. On
Wednesday, 50 years after ``South Pacific'' opened, Ms. Langee, 73,
will return to the Majestic Theatre's stage as a guest of the New
York-based Rodgers &AMP; Hammerstein Organization. ``I must say that
being on the Majestic stage again, just to stand there, is
exciting,'' she says. (Courtesy of Jackie Langee)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT12) GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- April 6, 1999 --
SOUTH-PACIFIC-ANNIVERSARY-1, 04-06 -- Jacqueline Langee - who was
part of the original cast - sits at her piano with an original
score from Rodgers and Hammerstein's ``South Pacific.'' She will
stand on stage at New York's Majestic Theatre for the first time in
nearly half a century Wednesday, 50 years after the musical opened.
``It's very exciting, but it's also sad,'' says Ms. Langee, 73, of
the reunion. (John Moran/Gainesville Sun Photo)
</P>
<P>
