QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-PRISONS-CHILDREN-NYT, which
moved in ``a'' news file.) 
c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``When children are not in contact with their parents, it is a
breeding ground for idealization, and when the parent is a big-time
criminal, they can turn them into legends.''
</P>
<P>
   _JAIME INCLAN, a clinical psychologist, on children who have a
parent in prison.
</P>
