<HEADLINE>
QB THOMAS LEAVES USC
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ As expected, USC freshman quarterback Jason Thomas
was granted his release Tuesday and is free to transfer to another
school.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas formally told USC coach Paul Hackett and athletic
director Mike Garrett during a meeting on campus that he wished to
leave.
</P>
<P>
   ``Disappointing day today,'' Hackett said. ``Too bad. It was
unfortunate. We wish him the very, very best. I just don't want to
play against him.
</P>
<P>
   ``We never got a chance to see the real Jason Thomas. There's
nothing that could have been done. He had the injury.''
</P>
<P>
   Jason Thomas redshirted this year after having surgery on his
left ankle to remove scar tissue. He fractured the ankle during his
senior year at Dominguez High.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas' brother, Charles Jr., who was also at the meeting, said
Jason has not yet decided where he will transfer.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's just trying to get over this,'' Charles said. ``He didn't
take it too well today.''
</P>
<P>
   Charles Thomas Jr. denied speculation that his brother has
already decided to transfer to Nevada-Las Vegas.
</P>
<P>
   ``He hasn't decided to go there,'' Charles said.
</P>
<P>
   Without Thomas, USC has only two scholarship quarterbacks _
sophomore Carson Palmer and junior Mike Van Raaphorst.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
