<HEADLINE>
CLIPPERS' TAYLOR STILL HOBBLING
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RANDY HILL  
 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ The bilateral Achilles tendinitis that has
discouraged Maurice Taylor from moving around to fetch rebounds
kept him in street clothes for Tuesday night's game with Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   ``Still sore, still tight,'' Taylor said while make a commute
from the locker room to the training room. ``But I'm shooting for
Thursday.''
</P>
<P>
   That's when the Clippers square off with Kevin Garnett and the
Minnesota Timberwolves at the Sports Arena.
</P>
<P>
   Rodney Rogers filled in for Taylor at power forward against the
Suns. Lorenzen Wright had played their in Taylor's absence Sunday,
finishing with 11 rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   Subhead Suns down
</P>
<P>
   A bruised right knee prevented Phoenix power forward Tom
Gugliotta from getting in his shots at the Clippers. Gugliotta
didn't make the trip.
</P>
<P>
   But rather than start veteran Danny Manning, Suns coach Danny
Ainge was expected to start rookie Pat Garrity in Gugilotta's place
to maintain the team's crucial substitution pattern.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns also were without shooting guard Rex Chapman, who
served the last mandatory game on the injured list thanks to a
turf-toe injury that somehow can be traced to the turf at America
West Arena.
</P>
